60|$|Then <b>she</b> <b>closed</b> <b>her</b> <b>eyes</b> <b>and</b> {{waited for}} the end. No slender shafts pierced her tender side. She raised her lids to see what stayed the hand of her executioners.|$|E
60|$|So she {{sat down}} {{in a corner of the}} coop, leaned her back against the slats, nodded at the {{friendly}} stars before <b>she</b> <b>closed</b> <b>her</b> <b>eyes,</b> <b>and</b> was asleep in half a minute.|$|E
